  "governanceRules": [
    "Every experimental cycle must declare the infrastructure profile on which its runs were executed.",
    "Infrastructure profiles live under config/infrastructure/profiles and are indexed through this registry.",
    "Results collected on different infrastructure profiles must not be interpreted as directly comparable unless the profile differences are explicitly reported.",
    "The historical C0/B0 results remain associated with INFRA_C0_1CP_2W_8C16G.",
    "C1/B1 must use a provider-backed profile, currently INFRA_C1_1CP_2W_8C16G unless explicitly replaced before execution.",
    "Provider-backed clusters must use GENAI_PB_REUSABLE_NODE_NAMING_V1 to avoid collisions with the historical sc-* cluster identity.",
    "Identical node names across two clusters do not imply identical infrastructure; infrastructureProfileId remains mandatory in cycle, baseline, run, and reporting metadata.",
    "Provider-backed profiles must resolve a provider binding before selecting a proxmox-k3s cluster YAML.",
    "Provider bindings live under config/infrastructure/providers/proxmox-k3s/bindings and are indexed through PROXMOX_K3S_PROVIDER_BINDINGS_INDEX.json.",
    "Redacted examples, local provider configs, and templates must remain separated.",
    "Infrastructure profile indexes must expose lifecycle policy metadata so cycle launchers can resolve reuse versus ephemeral behavior.",
    "Provider-backed infrastructure profiles must not be executed without a lifecycle manifest that records mode and destroy intent.",
    "Placement-variation cycles may use a cycle-scoped infrastructure profile that is intentionally equivalent to a previously validated infrastructure envelope, provided the equivalence and the dedicated provider config paths are explicit.",
    "C7 default-scheduler baseline profiles must not declare controlled placement profiles; pod placement must be produced by Kubernetes and captured as scheduler evidence.",
    "Default-scheduler baseline infrastructure profiles may reference provider bindings that are introduced by the provider-binding registry before execution."
  ],
